Just like the alleged homosexuality or mental disability of certain deportation victims.
The records of the concentration camps or arrest warrants established by the Gestapo had been gathered after war for a practical purpose: to find the deported or subject to compulsory work and, where appropriate, to provide proof of their detention, in order to open the way for their compensation.
